            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Radical State Convention</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Pennsylvania's Radical State Convention met in Philadelphia and nominated
                    John F. Hartranft for Auditor General and Jacob M. Campbell for Surveyor
                    General. The convention endorsed Grant for president and Andrew Curtin for vice
                    president. The paper gloats over the divisive arguments the endorsement of
                    Curtin caused.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
